accessrestrict.head: Conditions Governing Access
accessrestrict.p: Material more than 10 years old is open for research.
Negatives are restricted from access. Negatives of unique images will be available, with prior archival review.
Brittle or damaged items are available at the discretion of RAC.
Completion of a use agreement is required prior to providing scholarly access. See RAC Head of Reference (or applicable designee) for details.

userestrict.head: Conditions Governing Use
userestrict.p: Ford Foundation holds title, copyright and literary rights in the collection, in so far as it holds them.

The Rockefeller Archive Center has authority to grant permission to cite and publish material from the collection for scholarly purposes. Permission to publish extensive excerpts, or material in its entirety, will be referred to the Ford Foundation.

acqinfo.head: Immediate Source of Acquisition
acqinfo.p: Ford Foundation archive was deposited at RAC in 2011. Ford Foundation records, correspondence, reports, program files and officers papers were transferred to, and accessioned by, RAC beginning in 2011. Photographic holdings were transferred through multiple Accessions in 2012. Accessions continue as necessary.

prefercite.head: Preferred Citation
prefercite.p: Information regarding the Rockefeller Archive Center's preferred elements and forms of citation can be found at http://www.rockarch.org/research/citations.php.

arrangement.head: Arrangement
arrangement.p: Photographs are intellectually arranged into three series:
Series 2: Ford Foundation Trustees, Officers and Staff Photographs.
Series 3: General, Program, and Project Photographs.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents
scopecontent.p: This collection contains Jobs photos, as well as photographs of Ford Foundation trustees, officers, staff, and photographs of Foundation projects, programs and activities.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents
scopecontent.p: Milburn Lincoln Wilson (Director of the United States Extension Service at the U.S.D.A.) and his wife Ida, made two trips to India (in 1952-1953 and 1957-1958), at the invitation of Douglas Ensminger, the Ford Foundation?s Representative in India. The photographs in these files depict training programs in various Indian states, among other subjects. Countries and regions visited include: Rome, Greece, Turkey, Turkey Village trip, Iraq, Pakistan, Amritsar, India; Delhi, India; Punjab, India, Bophali, India; Hyderabad caves, India, Lucknow, India; Wiser trip, India; Allahabad, India; Agra, India, Taj Mahal and Fatehpur Sikri, Agra, India, Patna, Bihar, India, Jordan, Lebanon, Burma, Bangkok, Indonesia, Philippines, Japan, Hawaii.
